+# Iteration 2: Persistent Chrome — Implementation Plan
+
+> **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (recommended) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.
+
+**Goal:** Build the persistent app chrome — a real Tauri-native custom title bar (window controls wired to close/minimize/maximize) and the collapsible Sidebar with working screen-switching navigation — matching `design_handoff_secondboard/README.md` §6.1 pixel-for-pixel, per the recommended build order §11 step 2 ("Build persistent chrome (TitleBar + Sidebar) and the screen switcher").
+
+**Architecture:** Two new top-level Svelte components (`TitleBar`, `Sidebar`) composed from small presentational sub-components (`SidebarNavItem`, `SidebarSyncCard`, `SidebarProfile`) and a generic `Icon` primitive, wired to the existing `appState` rune store from Iteration 1 (`src/lib/stores/app-state.svelte.ts`). Window-chrome interactions (minimize/maximize/close) go through a thin `src/lib/api/window.ts` wrapper around `@tauri-apps/api/window` so components stay unit-testable without a real Tauri runtime. The root layout composes `TitleBar` + `Sidebar` + a scrollable main-content region; `+page.svelte` becomes a minimal per-screen placeholder so nav clicks are visibly wired end-to-end — real screen content (Board, Onboarding, Game Review, Dashboard, ...) is deferred to later iterations per README §11 steps 3-8.
+
+**Tech Stack:** SvelteKit 2.x + Svelte 5 (runes), TypeScript (strict), `@tauri-apps/api` (promoted to a runtime `dependency` this iteration since it's now imported by shipped frontend code), Vitest + `@testing-library/svelte` for component tests.
+
+## Global Constraints
+
+- **Zero visual deviation** — every color/size/radius/gap in this plan is copied verbatim from `design_handoff_secondboard/README.md` §6.1 and `design_handoff_secondboard/reference/SecondBoard.dc.html` lines 33-109 and 1200-1211 (title bar, sidebar, nav array). Do not approximate.
+- **Exact nav data** — the 9 nav entries (id/label/icon SVG path) are copied verbatim from `SecondBoard.dc.html`'s `nav` array (lines 1200-1209). Do not "clean up" or re-derive icon paths.
+- **Svelte 5 runes only** — components use `$props()` / `$derived` / `$state` as established by `svelte.config.js`'s forced runes mode (Iteration 1, Task 1).
+- **TypeScript strict mode**; no `any` in new code (enforced by `eslint.config.js`'s `@typescript-eslint/no-explicit-any: error`).
+- **`appState` is a shared singleton** (`src/lib/stores/app-state.svelte.ts`, module-level `$state`) — reused across the whole app *and* across test files in the same Vitest run. Any test that reads or writes it must reset it in `beforeEach` via `Object.assign(appState, createAppState())` to avoid cross-test pollution.
+- **Window-chrome calls go through `src/lib/api/window.ts`**, never imported directly from `@tauri-apps/api/window` in a component — this keeps components unit-testable without mocking Tauri runtime internals, and matches the `api/` module's role as the Tauri-facing wrapper layer (Iteration 1, Task 2).
+- **No real screen content yet.** Onboarding/Dashboard/Game Review/Opening Explorer/Insights/Training bodies stay one-line text placeholders. Iteration 2 is chrome + navigation only — building any real screen body now would violate README §11's vertical-slice build order (Board is step 3, Game Review is step 4, etc.).
+- **Environment note (same as Iteration 1):** this machine has Node v24.13.1/npm 11.8.0 and Rust 1.97.0 installed at `C:\Users\JW\.cargo\bin`, which is **not** on PATH inside the Bash (Git Bash) tool's shell. Use the PowerShell tool for any `cargo`/`rustc`/`tauri` CLI command, or prefix Bash commands with `export PATH="$PATH:/c/Users/JW/.cargo/bin"`. `npm`/`npx`/`vitest`/`eslint` work fine in either shell.
+- **Commit after every task.** Conventional commit prefixes (`feat:`, `chore:`, `test:`).
